## ⚙️ Installation & Setup

### 1️⃣ Clone Repository

```
git clone https://github.com/YTManish/Campus-Lost-Found-Portal.git
cd Campus-Lost-Found-Portal
```

---

### 2️⃣ Install Backend Dependencies

```
cd backend
npm install
```

---

### 3️⃣ Run Server

```
node server.js
```

Server runs on:

```
http://localhost:3000
```

---

### 4️⃣ Open Frontend

Use Live Server OR open:

```
login.html
```

---

## 🗄 Database Setup

### Option 1: Local MongoDB

🔹 Local MongoDB Setup

If you are running MongoDB locally:

Make sure MongoDB service is running

Use this connection string in server.js:

mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/lostfound
Database will be automatically created when data is inserted

📦 Collections Used

This project uses:

users → Stores user details & roles
items → Stores lost/found items

## 🔑 Admin Login

To access admin panel:

1. Create a user
2. Manually change role in MongoDB:

```
role: "admin"
```

Then login → redirected to Admin Panel

---

## 📦 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint     | Description   |
| ------ | ------------ | ------------- |
| POST   | /register    | Register user |
| POST   | /login       | Login user    |
| POST   | /add-item    | Add item      |
| GET    | /items       | Get all items |
| POST   | /claim       | Request claim |
| POST   | /approve     | Approve claim |
| POST   | /reject      | Reject claim  |
| POST   | /delete-item | Delete item   |
| GET    | /users       | Get users     |
| POST   | /delete-user | Delete user   |

---

## ⚠️ Notes

* Image uploads stored in `/uploads`
* Do not upload `node_modules` to GitHub
* Use `.gitignore` for clean repo

---

## 🌍 Deployment

* Backend: Railway / Render / Vercel (serverless)
* Database: MongoDB Atlas
* Frontend: Can be hosted separately


